Former Abia Governor, Orji Kalu, has on Wednesday responded to calls for him to declare his 2023 presidential ambition. Kalu says he is being urged to publicly announce his intention and commence consultations. In a statement, via his Facebook page, he wrote, “I have been inundated with pressured requests to also declare my intention to run for the Presidency of our dear country and visit Mr. President following visits by my other brothers to Mr. President yesterday. FG Strengthens Health Regulatory Agencies To Actualise Mandate –… Osun Guber: PDP Screens Adeleke, Ogunbiyi, Others “I have taken off time to inform ourselves through the media that as a party man who believes in the supremacy of our party. “I shall as soon as the party zones the Presidency and southern Nigeria is zoned to produce the Presidential candidate of our party. “My train which is already steaming shall take off with a visit to Aso Rock Villa and brief Mr. President of our collective decision”, Kalu wrote.